NO CONTEST plea entered to the charge, theft-business setting.  Convicted.
EXHIBIT 1, copy of Release of Claims, marked.
Sentence Withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for five (5) years.
Conditions of probation:
1) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
2) Pay restitution in an amount to be determined and to be repaid at a rate to be determined by the agent; 
3) Spend one hundred twenty (120) days in the county jail, under the Huber Law, commencing on 05-01-16 by 8:00 a.m.;
4) Defendant must maintain fulltime employment, work search or combination, but is prohibited from handling money or accounts payable, also to include volunteer work;
5) Defendant is not to possess any credit cards;
6) No contact with Invincible Office Furniture;
7) Complete one hundred (100) hours community service;
8) Provide DNA sample/surcharge;
9) Pay court costs;
10) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
11) undergo counseling as deemed appropriate by the agent, including financial counseling.
Scheduling conference is set for 04-07-16 at 3:30 p.m. to set a restitution hearing.
